The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Monday, November 8, 2004

 Road to avoid

 SP Mukherjee Road, near Rashbehari Avenue crossing. Dug up for pipeline work.

 Club plans

 The 175th year celebration plans of the Royal Calcutta Golf Club, presented by Airtel in association with The Telegraph, to be unveiled at ITC Sonar Bangla, at noon. 

 Soiree

 Rabindrasangeet exponent from Bangladesh Shama Rahman will perform at Bioscope, Swabhumi, 6.30 pm.

 Fashion

 Tantu 2004, the graduation event of textile design students of National Institute of Fashion Technology, at The Park, 6 pm.

 The Diwali Fiesta, showcasing contemporary collection of westerns, kurtas, saris and lehngas, at The Conclave, 11 am to 1 pm.

 Consumer

 Consumer 2004, a fair on the Maidan, 11 am to 8 pm.

 Dance

 A workshop on Odissi dance, conducted by Ratikanta Mahapatra, at Savarmati Dance amp; Music Centre, 114/Y, Raja SC Mullick Road, from 10 am to 7 pm.

 Exhibition

 An exhibition of colonial furniture, affordable art and Northeast tribal handloom at 2/1, Loudon Street, 11 am to 7 pm.




